S3 : Interactive maps with leaflet

Leaflet

Leaflet is a powerful javascript based tool that can be used to create interactive maps - like google maps. Get more information at: https://nceas.github.io/oss-lessons/publishing-maps-to-the-web-in-r/publishing-maps-to-the-web-in-r.html

library(raster)
## Loading required package: sp
library(leaflet)

paramuriceaClavata <- read.csv("Data/dataBases/Paramuricea_clavata.csv",sep=";",header=TRUE)
colnames(paramuriceaClavata)
## [1] "X"              "Species"        "Location"       "Year"          
## [5] "Lon"            "Lat"            "Depth"          "Main.reference"
m <- leaflet()
m <- addTiles(m)
m <- addCircleMarkers(m, 
                      lng=paramuriceaClavata[,"Lon"], 
                      lat=paramuriceaClavata[,"Lat"] )
m
mpa <- shapefile("Data/vectorShapefiles/noTakeMPA/MPA.shp")

m <- leaflet()
m <- addTiles(m)
m <- setView(m, lng=20, lat=35, zoom=3)
m <- addCircleMarkers(m, 
                      lng=paramuriceaClavata[,"Lon"], 
                      lat=paramuriceaClavata[,"Lat"],
                      popup= paste0("Reference: ", paramuriceaClavata[,"Main.reference"]) , 
                      radius = 3, 
                      color = "Red" , 
                      stroke = FALSE, 
                      fillOpacity = 1 )
m <- addPolygons(m,data=mpa,color = "Black", stroke = 2 , weight = 3)
m
